{# Quick start #}
<h2>Quick start</h2>

<h3>Web projects</h3>
<p class="wmre-col-md-3-4">
  Getting started is as simple as including West Midlands Rail Executive Design System's minified CSS file and adding <code class="wmre-website-inline-code">.wmre-html</code> to the html element in your service/application.
</p>
<pre>
  <code class="html wmre-show-more-ignore">
  {%- filter forceescape %}
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html lang="en-gb" class="wmre-html">
    <head>
      <!-- CSS for WMRE Design System -->
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="$*cdn/css/wmre-components.min.css" />
    </head>
    <body>
      <!-- site content... -->
    </body>
  </html>
  {%- endfilter %}
  </code>
</pre>

<h3>Want to use our icons, or using a component that references an icon?</h3>
<p>Please see the
  {{
    wmreLink({
      link: "$*baseUrl/styles/icons/",
      linkTitle: "Using WMRE Design System icons",
      text: "icons page"
    })
  }}.
</p>

<h3>Mobile app projects (React Native)</h3>
<p>If you are using React Native, you can import our styles like below.</p>
<pre>
  <code class="javascript">
    {% filter forceescape %}// Import react native styles for WMRE Design System
    import wmreStyles from "$*cdn/css/react-native/wmre-components.min.js"
    {%- endfilter %}
  </code>
</pre>
